<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="idefaef4da-3a6e-11f1-addd-bbaf0b3f68e9" identifier="/us/usc/t7/s3416"><num value="3416">§ 3416.</num><heading> Amendments to orders</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">The provisions of this chapter applicable to orders shall be applicable to amendments to orders.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="idefaef4db-3a6e-11f1-addd-bbaf0b3f68e9">(<ref href="/us/pl/95/113/tXVII/s1717">Pub. L. 95–113, title XVII, § 1717</ref>, <date date="1977-09-29">Sept. 29, 1977</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/91/1040">91 Stat. 1040</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
<notes type="uscNote" id="idefaef4dc-3a6e-11f1-addd-bbaf0b3f68e9">
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" role="crossHeading" topic="statutoryNotes" id="idefaef4dd-3a6e-11f1-addd-bbaf0b3f68e9"><heading class="centered"><b>Statutory Notes and Related Subsidiaries</b></heading></note>
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" topic="effectiveDate" id="idefaef4de-3a6e-11f1-addd-bbaf0b3f68e9"><heading class="centered smallCaps">Effective Date</heading><p style="-uslm-lc:I21" class="indent0">Section effective <date date="1977-10-01">Oct. 1, 1977</date>, see <ref href="/us/pl/95/113/s1901">section 1901 of Pub. L. 95–113</ref>, set out as an Effective Date of 1977 Amendment note under <ref href="/us/usc/t7/s1307">section 1307 of this title</ref>.</p>
</note>
